Here&#39;s a piece of advice, whether you want it or not.  This &#39;LISTEN&#39;
method of yours sounds like a reverse GET.  The RESTful solution is not
to violate the uniform interface by creating an unspecified new method
nobody has ever heard of.

The RESTful solution would be to support an evolving standard like
rHTTP, which makes use of HTTP&#39;s &#39;Upgrade&#39; facility to reverse the
direction of the transaction.  The method would still be GET, for a
uniform interface.

